---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Eight-Letter Bingos in Scrabble — Advanced Bonus Words"
  description="Master eight-letter bingos in Scrabble. Learn how to extend 7-letter words, find 8-letter plays through hooks, and score massive bonuses with advanced tile management."
  keywords="eight letter bingos scrabble, 8 letter scrabble words, eight letter words bonus, scrabble bingo 8 letters, advanced scrabble bingos, long word scrabble strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Eight-Letter Bingos in Scrabble — Advanced Bonus Words",
    "description": "Master eight-letter bingos in Scrabble. Learn how to extend 7-letter words and find 8-letter plays through hooks.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/eight-letter-bingos" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you play an 8-letter bingo in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "An 8-letter bingo is played by using all 7 tiles from your rack plus one tile already on the board. You hook your tiles onto an existing letter to form an 8-letter word. This still earns the 50-point bonus since you played all 7 rack tiles." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are 8-letter bingos more valuable than 7-letter bingos?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Often yes. 8-letter bingos score the same 50-point bonus but tend to cover more premium squares since they span more of the board. The average 8-letter bingo scores 75-90 points compared to 65-80 for 7-letter bingos." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the most common 8-letter bingos?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Common 8-letter bingos include TRAINERS, PAINTERS, NOTARIES, SENORITA, RELATION, ORIENTAL, TAILORED, and DETAINER. These words use common letters and can be formed by hooking through frequently-placed board tiles like S, E, R, and D." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Bingo Topics</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Eight-Letter Bingos: Advanced Bonus Words for Competitive Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Eight-letter bingos represent a step up from standard 7-letter plays. By hooking all 7 of your rack tiles through a letter already on the board, you create longer words that cover more premium squares and often score higher. Mastering 8-letter bingos separates club players from tournament contenders.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How 8-Letter Bingos Work</h2>
      <p>Unlike a 7-letter bingo where you place all tiles independently, an 8-letter bingo uses a letter already on the board as part of the word. You still play all 7 rack tiles, so you still earn the 50-point bonus.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Hook Principle</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Your 7 tiles + 1 board tile = 8-letter word. The board tile acts as a <span class="text-white font-medium">"hook"</span> that your word passes through. The most common hooks are <span class="text-white font-medium">S, E, R, D, and N</span> — letters that appear frequently in word endings and middles.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">29,000+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid 8-letter words (TWL)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">75-90</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg points per 8-letter bingo</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">50</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bonus (same as 7-letter)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 8-Letter Bingo Words</h2>
      <p>These are the most frequently played 8-letter bingos in tournament Scrabble, all using common tiles:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOTARIES</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">58+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SENORITA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">58+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RELATION</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">58+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ORIENTAL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">58+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TRAINERS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">58+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PAINTERS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">60+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAILORED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">59+50</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DETAINER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">59+50</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Finding 8-Letter Bingos on the Board</h2>
      <p>The key to playing 8-letter bingos is scanning the board for usable hook letters:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Board Scanning Process</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Identify exposed letters</span> — find board tiles with 7+ empty squares in a row/column passing through them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Test each hook letter</span> — mentally add the board letter to your 7 rack tiles and check for 8-letter words.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Check placement</span> — verify the word fits without creating invalid cross-words in adjacent rows/columns.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Calculate score</span> — include premium squares covered by your tiles (the board letter's premium was already scored).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Common Prefixes and Suffixes</h2>
      <p>Many 8-letter bingos are formed by adding common prefixes or suffixes to shorter words:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Common Prefixes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RE- (RETAINER, RELATION), UN- (UNRAISED, UNSERIAL), OUT- (OUTRAISE, OUTEARNS), OVER- (OVERCAST)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Common Suffixes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">-ING (TRAINING, DRAINING), -TION (RELATION, ROTATION), -ERS (TRAINERS, PAINTERS), -ED (TAILORED, DETAILED)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">8-Letter vs 7-Letter: When to Choose</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Choose 8-letter when:</span> The hook letter sits near a Triple Word Score, giving you premium square access that a standalone 7-letter word can't reach.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Choose 7-letter when:</span> You have a clear open lane that scores equally or the 8-letter placement creates dangerous openings for your opponent.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Always check both:</span> Tournament players calculate scores for all available bingo placements before choosing. A 7-letter bingo on a Triple Word can outscore an 8-letter bingo elsewhere.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Key Takeaways</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Summary</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Eight-letter bingos use <span class="text-white font-medium">7 rack tiles + 1 board tile</span> for the same 50-point bonus but often higher total scores. Learn to scan for hook letters (S, E, R, D, N), memorise common prefix/suffix patterns, and always compare 8-letter options against available 7-letter plays before committing.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/seven-letter-bingo-list" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Seven-Letter Bingo List</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/hooking-existing-words" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Hooking Existing Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/bingo-stem-strategy" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Bingo Stem Strategy</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find 8-letter words from your tiles — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
